at least become virtuous.
[deletion]&[/deletion] [deletion]his mind will be formed[/deletion]
[deletion]by good & regular habits[/deletion]. –
His disposition at present
is good; but his habits are
irregular. These habits you
will easily correct without
pain; at a future
period he will thank
you – & if indeed the
benefits He may derive
from you are at all
analogous to those which
his brother has derived
He will never forget
his instructor – –

